  "name": "Incubation Portfolio Optimization Pipeline",
  "description": "Replication code for a predictive modeling and multiobjective optimization pipeline for evidence-based incubation portfolio selection under public policy constraints. Implements ElasticNet-penalized logistic regression with leave-one-out cross-validation, epsilon-constraint MILP optimization to trace Pareto frontiers across policy-relevant objectives, and Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation for small-sample cohort data. Designed for university incubators operating under government-mandated accountability frameworks such as Brazil's CERNE accreditation system.",
